#IndiaFightsCorona The entire human race is in crisis around the world. PM Modi appreciated the patience of 130 crore Indians who have vigorously fought the Corona global epidemic by taking necessary precautions so far. via NaMo App

#IndiaFightsCorona When a political crisis or a natural disaster occurs it is generally restricted to a few countries.But this time it has engulfed the whole world. PMModi asserted that even World War I and World War II did not involve as many countries as Coronavirus has.

#IndiaFightsCorona PM Modi urged every Indian to be aware and alert amongst the COVID-19 rumours. A belief that the global pandemic Coronavirus is something that can be taken lightly is not correct. via NaMo App

#IndiaFightsCorona For a developing country like India  PM Modi says combating Corona is a big challenge. He requested two important things from 130 crore to tackle COVID-19- Sankalp(resolve) and Sayyam(restraint) via NaMo App
#IndiaFightsCorona Making every Indian remain vigilant and responsible  PM Modi urges the 130 crore Indians to social distance themselves for a few weeks. via NaMo App
#IndiaFightsCorona Amidst the COVID-19 wave  PM Modi makes a call of "Hum Swasth to Jag Swasth” -If we're healthy  the world is healthy and requests everyone to remain healthy. via NaMo App
#IndiaFightsCorona PM Modi made a special request to the senior citizens to not venture out of their homes and stay safe. via NaMo App
#IndiaFightsCorona PM Modi requests Indians to not hoard essential commodities due to panic and assures that the country will not run short of supplies. via NaMo App

#IndiaFightsCorona PMModi requested co-operation from 130crore Indians on March22nd to express gratitude to everyone who has selflessly served the country.The manner of thanksgiving would be by clapping hands at 5pm for 5mins at the doors/balconies of our residence. via NaMo App

#IndiaFightsCorona As a preventive measure to stop the economy from being affected deeply by this pandemic  the Modi Govt sets up a COVID-19 Economic Response Task Force under the Finance Minister. via NaMo App

#IndiaFightsCorona As a special call to action  PM Modi requests 130 crore Indians to impose a Janta Curfew on 22nd March from between 7am-9pm. This is a self-imposed  self-regulated curfew where the citizens will refrain from stepping out of their residence. via NaMo App

#IndiaFightsCorona India is undertaking evacuation operations from several countries in the wake of the COVID-19 outbreak. Over 1 000 Indian Nationals have been evacuated from several parts of the world. via NaMo App

#IndiaFightsCorona Assisting its neighbouring countries  India pledged $10 million towards a Covid-19 emergency fund along with a rapid response team of doctors and specialists for SAARC Nations. via NaMo App

#IndiaFightsCorona India has set up an Integrated Disease Surveillance Portal to better trace possible virus carriers and the people they contacted. PM Modi offered to share this technology with SAARC partners besides providing training on using it. via NaMo App

#IndiaFightsCorona India is helping its neighbours with medical supplies amidst the corona outbreak. Medical supplies have been sent to Maldives  Bhutan  and Afghanistan among other countries. via NaMo App
